ne, Tissue, Sample, Rep, Reference_genome, Total_reads,\nPassing_filtering, All_mapped_reads, Uniquely_mapped_reads`. The read-count columns\nare formatted as `<count> (<pct>%)`; only the numeric prefix matters.\n\nRender a two-panel PDF at `output/mapping_stats.pdf` (landscape, 10x12 in) with\nstacked fill/stack bars per (Line/Tissue/Sample/Rep) showing the breakdown into\nUniquely mapped / Multi-mapping / Unmapped / Filtered reads, faceted by `Line`,\nwith the title `Mapping statistics for ChIP_demo samples`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/mapping_stats.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mapping_stats.pdf under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mapping_stats.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mapping_stats.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mapping_stats.pdf` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ZZbuSD2o3HTAiUWt6VBGdYFQ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input TSV file to extract the mapping statistics data.\\n2. Parse the read-count columns to extract numeric values.\\n3. Calculate the breakdown of reads into Uniquely mapped, Multi-mapping, Unmapped, and Filtered reads.\\n4. Create a stacked bar plot for each (Line/Tissue/Sample/Rep) combination, faceted by Line.\\n5. Render the plots into a two-panel PDF with the specified dimensions and title.\\n6. Save the PDF to the output directory.\\n7. Verify the existence of the PDF and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (512 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_ZZbuSD2o3HTAiUWt6VBGdYFQ"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_2mxZPB4Fio88dOrc2VzzfaBG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/mapping_stats.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Line\tTissue\tSample\tRep\tReference_genome\tTotal_reads\tPassing_filtering\tAll_mapped_reads\tUniquely_mapped_reads\nB73\tleaf\tH3K27ac\trep1\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t36455603\t32486794 (89.1%)\t30504646 (83.7%)\t22996726 (63.1%)\nB73\tleaf\tH3K27ac\trep2\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t19682115\t18769792 (95.4%)\t17478504 (88.8%)\t15665624 (79.6%)\nB73\tleaf\tH3K4me3\trep1\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t17917183\t16825117 (93.9%)\t14365519 (80.2%)\t10351979 (57.8%)\nB73\tleaf\tH3K4me3\trep2\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t22806804\t21222541 (93.1%)\t18106739 (79.4%)\t13466783 (59.0%)\nMo17\tleaf\tH3K27ac\trep1\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t36806503\t34971054 (95.0%)\t31485921 (85.5%)\t25151772 (68.3%)\nMo17\tleaf\tH3K27ac\trep2\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t24334531\t23384098 (96.1%)\t19894719 (81.8%)\t17453243 (71.7%)\nMo17\troot\tH3K4me3\trep1\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t38425670\t35438513 (92.2%)\t31304417 (81.5%)\t23395951 (60.9%)\nMo17\troot\tH3K4me3\trep2\tZm-B73-REFERENCE-NAM-5.0\t26294238\t23407683 (89.0%)\t20963716 (79.7%)\t16330220 (62.1%)\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_2mxZPB4Fio88dOrc2VzzfaBG"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Zmt7KS3Hne87E8wejTOaD5oA", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(ggplot2)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(gridExtra)\\n\\n# Read the data\\ndata <- read.delim('input/mapping_stats.tsv')\\n\\n# Extract numeric values from the columns\\nextract_numeric <- function(x) as.numeric(sub(' .*', '', x))\\ndata <- data %>% mutate(\\n  Total_reads = extract_numeric(Total_reads),\\n  Passing_filtering = extract_numeric(Passing_filtering),\\n  All_mapped_reads = extract_numeric(All_mapped_reads),\\n  Uniquely_mapped_reads = extract_numeric(Uniquely_mapped_reads)\\n)\\n\\n# Calculate breakdown\\nfiltered_reads <- data$Total_reads - data$Passing_filtering\\nunmapped_reads <- data$Passing_filtering - data$All_mapped_reads\\nduplicated_reads <- data$All_mapped_reads - data$Uniquely_mapped_reads\\n\\n# Prepare data for plotting\\ndata_long <- data %>%\\n  mutate(\\n    Filtered_reads = filtered_reads,\\n    Unmapped_reads = unmapped_reads,\\n    Multi_mapping_reads = duplicated_reads\\n  ) %>%\\n  select(Line, Tissue, Sample, Rep, Uniquely_mapped_reads, Multi_mapping_reads, Unmapped_reads, Filtered_reads) %>%\\n  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with(\\\"Uniquely_mapped_reads\\\"), names_to = \\\"Type\\\", values_to = \\\"Count\\\")\\n\\n# Plot\\nplot <- ggplot(data_long, aes(x = interaction(Tissue, Sample, Rep), y = Count, fill = Type)) +\\n  geom_bar(stat = \\\"identity\\\") +\\n  facet_wrap(~ Line, scales = \\\"free_x\\\") +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +\\n  labs(title = \\\"Mapping statistics for ChIP_demo samples\\\", x = \\\"Sample\\\", y = \\\"Read Count\\\")\\n\\n# Save the plot\\npdf(\\\"output/mapping_stats.pdf\\\", width = 10, height = 12)\\nprint(plot)\\ndev.off()\\n\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=0\nstdout:\nnull device \n          1 \n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    filter, lag\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018gridExtra\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:dplyr\u2019:\n\n    combine\n\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_Zmt7KS3Hne87E8wejTOaD5oA"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_tZrz